cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with feature selection, which is an important preprocessing step for many pattern classification tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the shift in the target of classification system design from seeking maximum classification accuracy to maximum AUC/MAUC, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. 

The paper also touches upon topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it discusses classification systems and their performance metrics. 

Furthermore, the paper involves the use of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms to develop a new feature selection method. 

Lastly, the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the design of classification systems and their performance optimization.
